			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: IM &amp;amp; SM Questions<a name="27904"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 15 04 7:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You get the instrumental boost even without an instrument equipt.
<br />

<br />
For instance:
<br />
Epic + IM3 = 1.0 (base) + 0.8 (epic) + 0.6 (IM3) = 2.4
<br />
nekkid + IM3 = 1.0 (base) + 0.6 (IM3) = 1.6
<br />

<br />
But it only works for songs that do NOT use the Singing skill.  Using instrument or not does not matter, its the type of song that it the determining factor on whether or not IM is used.
<br />

<br />
Same goes for SM, but in reverse.  It only helps Singing based songs, whether you have a Voice &quot;instrument&quot; (Epic or whatever) or not.
<br />

<br />
---
<br />

<br />
Basically, it comes down to this:
<br />
IM3 <b>always</b> gives you a +0.6 to your instrumental mods.
<br />
SM3 <b>always</b> gives you a +0.6 to your Singing mod.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
